<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="80.[189,454,923,949]" box="[189,454,923,949]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,923,949]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,923,949]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="80.[189,1399,971,1179]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,597,971,997]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigella" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,301,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[320,498,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Montanocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[516,597,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">nigella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[606,699,971,997]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the characters like dense, long pilosity of body, big size, broad body and structure of male genitalia with the other members of the subgenus. Among the Nepalese taxa 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[364,540,1043,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigella" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[364,391,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[408,441,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[459,540,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">nigella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,641,1044,1070]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[867,1123,1043,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevimontana" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[867,894,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[911,943,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[961,1123,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">brevimontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1133,1226,1044,1070]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs by having mostly yellow pilosity of scutellum (vs black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[827,1020,1080,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevimontana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[827,1020,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">C. brevimontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1027,1120,1080,1106]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), mostly orange pilosity of abdomen (vs mainly yellowish in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[632,831,1116,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevimontana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[632,831,1116,1142]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">C. brevimontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[839,933,1116,1143]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and brownish basal parts of tibiae (vs black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,486,1152,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevimontana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[290,486,1152,1179]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">C. brevimontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[493,588,1153,1179]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1399,1219,1293]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="80.[189,324,1219,1245]" box="[189,324,1219,1245]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1219,1245]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1219,1245]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="80.[189,1399,1267,1293]" box="[189,1399,1267,1293]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[627,720,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">nigellus</emphasis>
’and is the diminutive form of ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1083,1145,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">niger</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘blackish’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
